{
  "stem": "11998.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was working in a shoe factory that was making and repairing miners' shoes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we were walking and every time when we got back to the ghetto we never knew whether they would have an [NON-ENGLISH] or a deportation.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They would just come in, they surround the ghetto and they go through the streets and they would go from house to house and search whoever they could find.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Children, young men, women, or old men and that was the only people that were left in the ghetto at that time because the workforce was working out in the factories.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we never knew who was left when we returned back to ghetto of ours, because my mother and my sister did not work.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the other way around.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After we were deported to Srodula, we came back from Srodula to work in Sosnoweic.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now I don't remember the exact date.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember if it was in the fall of 1942, or whether it was in the early spring of 1943.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only thing that I remember is that it was cold and it was muddy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had to walk through that mud to get to our house, So I must imagine it would be in either the very early spring or sometime in the winter of 1942.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was about half an hour, maybe three quarters of an hour walk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We walked in one column with the Jewish police guarding us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Srodula was not-- it wasn't barbed wired.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was also not--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was also an open ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a ghetto but it was surrounded by fields.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was more difficult to-- they had patrols.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nazi patrols going around the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
